The paper deals with the problem of learning with drifting distributions, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper presents new learning bounds and a new algorithm for this problem. The paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
